e Priestly Source offers a distinctive account of the origins of the people of Israel and a unique perspective on their relationship with their god, Yahweh—one in stark contrast to what is found when we read the Bible now. With a translation by Liane Feldman, an authority on the text, The Consuming Fire reveals the mythical foundation for the practice of sacrifice in ancient Israelite and Jewish religion. By presenting this fascinating material on its own, The Consuming Fire offers an opportunity to expand our understanding of ancient traditions and to find something new and beautiful at the source.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 7aRELIGION / Bible / General.2bisacsh  aAncient.  aBible reconstructed.  aJewish history.  aPriestly Narrative.  aYahweh.  abook of the Israeiltes.  acivilization.  acreation myths.  afor the first time.  aliterary.  aorigins story.  apeople of Israel.  areligious practices.  aunknown classic.  aworld literature.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079134140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520383661?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520383661423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520383661/original  a978-3-11-079134-1  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY